Please note that third parties (including, for example, advertising networks and providers of external services like web traffic analysis services) may also use cookies, over which we have no control. These cookies are likely to be analytical/performance cookies or targeting cookies.
You can block cookies by activating the setting on your browser that allows you to refuse the setting of all or some cookies. However, if you use your browser settings to block all cookies (including essential cookies) you may not be able to access all or parts of our site.
WHY WE NEED THIS INFORMATION: Contractual purposes
We collect information about you, your boat and your location in order to provide the Services and for the App to function. This includes, but is not limited to disclosing data (including personal data) to third parties for the purpose of preserving life and property at sea.
Without this information the App is unable to operate as it is intended to.
WHY WE NEED THIS INFORMATION: Legitimate interests
We may also process your personal information in pursuit of our legitimate interests:
to notify you of any changes or proposed changes in any laws, regulations or best practice in relation to boating, yachting and other related activities which we feel may be of interest to you;
to ask questions for the purposes of market research, where it is deemed appropriate;
to provide you with information about other goods and services which may be of interest to you.
In relation to the operation of the App:
to ensure that content from the site is presented in the most effective manner for you and for your computer or mobile device.
to administer the site and for internal operations, including troubleshooting, data analysis, testing, research, statistical and survey purposes;
to identify and implement improvements in the operation of the site, the content included on the site and the way in which content is presented;
to allow you to participate in interactive features of the site, when you choose to do so;
as part of our efforts to keep the site safe and secure;
to measure or understand the effectiveness and relevance of advertising on the site
We will only process your personal information for our legitimate interests when we believe our own interests are not overridden by your own rights and interest.
Where we process your personal information in pursuit of our legitimate interest, you have the right to object to us using your personal information for those purposes. If you wish to object to any of the above processing, please contact
dpo@rya.org.uk
.
OTHER USES OF THE INFORMATION COLLECTED
We also compile and may publish statistics and analytical data gathered from the data, which you submit to us or which is gathered by the App so as to identify broad user trends and vessel traffic intensity in support of the RYA's work to represent and protect the interests of recreational boaters. Such statistics and analytical data will not be compiled or published in a form which specifically identifies you, the people on your boat or your boat.
WHERE WE STORE YOUR PERSONAL DATA AND SECURITY
The data that we collect from you is stored on a secure server located in the United Kingdom. Your data may be processed by  third parties such as website hosting providers, third party storage providers, and by staff of those operating on behalf of such third parties Your data may also be transferred to, and subsequently stored by third parties in accordance with the provision of the Services, as explained in more detail below. . We will take all steps reasonably necessary to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this privacy policy.
Where you have chosen a password that enables you to access certain parts of the Website, you are responsible for keeping this password confidential. We ask you not to share a password with anyone.
Unfortunately, the transmission of information via the internet is not completely secure. Although we will do our best to protect your personal data, we cannot guarantee the security of your data transmitted to or from the Website or the App; any transmission is at your own risk. Once we have received your information, we will use strict procedures and security features to try to prevent unauthorised access.
We may collect and store personal data on your Device using application data caches and browser web storage and other technology.
DISCLOSURE OF YOUR INFORMATION
Given the nature and purpose of the Services and the App, you acknowledge  that it is necessary for us to share some or all of the personal data which you submit (including location data) with the following parties for the purposes of providing the Services:
HM Coastguard
the European Maritime Safety Agency ("
EMSA
");
emergency services including national coast guards, police and ambulance services;
the providers of search and rescue services (including voluntary services);
third party technical service providers (including telecommunications companies); and
any other parties or authorities which may be able to assist in the preservation of life and property at sea.
You also acknowledge that in some circumstance it may be necessary to transfer personal data to organisations located outside of the EEA, if this is required for the provision of the Services, for instance if an alert is sent while you are outside of the EEA.
We may also disclose your personal information to third parties:
If we are under a duty to disclose or share your personal data in order to comply with any legal or regulatory obligation or request.
In order to:
enforce or apply the EULA, and other agreements or to investigate potential breaches; or
protect the rights, property or safety of, you, the RYA, our customers, or others. This includes exchanging information with other companies and organisations for the purposes of fraud protection.
THIRD PARTY WEBSITES
The Website may, from time to time, contain links to and from the websites of our partner networks, advertisers and affiliates (including, but not limited to, websites on which the App or the Services are advertised). If you follow a link to any of these websites, please note that these websites and any services that may be accessible through them have their own privacy policies and that we do not accept any responsibility or liability for these policies or for any personal data that may be collected through these websites or services, such as contact and location data. Please check these policies before you submit any personal data to these websites or use these services.
YOUR RIGHTS
You have the following rights in relation to the personal information we hold about you:
to access your personal data
to be provided with information about how your personal data is processed
to have your personal data corrected
to have your personal data erased in certain circumstances
to object to or restrict how your personal data is processed
to have your personal data transferred to yourself or to another business in certain circumstances.
In many cases you can exercise these rights by logging on to [ your SafeTrx  account ]   and making changes to your profile.  Alternatively, you can contact the RYAâ€™s Data Protection Officer on
DPO@rya.org.uk
You have the right to take any complaints about how we process your personal data to the Information Commissioner:
